OL,3,CPolice officer who shot man thought to
OL,4,Cbe a terrorist speaks for first time
OL,6,F"Because of his actions, what he did,
OL,7,Fthe information we received, it left
OL,8,Fme with no other conclusion than I had
OL,9,Fto act or we were going to die."
OL,11,FC12 added that the way Mr De Menezes
OL,12,Fstood up while on the train
OL,13,F"triggered" something in his head.
OL,15,F"He knew who we were. He still
OL,16,Fcontinued on his forward momentum as I
OL,17,Fhad my weapon up, pointing at his
OL,18,Fhead," he recalled.
